                  "answerKey": "answer_2",
                  "content": "their low productivity"
                },
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_3",
                  "content": "the amount of property space required"
                },
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_4",
                  "content": "their automated nature"
                }
              ]
            },
            "answerKey": {
              "assessmentType": "multiplechoice",
              "answers": {
                "answer_3": {
                  "score": 0.0,
                  "response": "Consider This: Henry Bessemer in England and William Kelly in the United States developed the Bessemer process, which resulted in more uniform and durable steel. Earlier methods produced amounts a person could lift. A Bessemer converter handled 5 tons of molten metal at a time. The mass production of steel was now possible. See L.O. 18.2 What were the main characteristics of the new steel and oil industries?"
                },
